{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:romans.3",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "romans",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Romans 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Romans 3 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:1",
      "text": "What advantage then hath the Jew? or what profit is there of circumcision?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:2",
      "text": "Much every way: chiefly, because that unto them were committed the oracles of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:3",
      "text": "For what if some did not believe? shall their unbelief make the faith of God without effect?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:4",
      "text": "God forbid: yea, let God be true, but every man a liar; as it is written, That thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:5",
      "text": "But if our unrighteousness commend the righteousness of God, what shall we say? Is God unrighteous who taketh vengeance? (I speak as a man)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:6",
      "text": "God forbid: for then how shall God judge the world?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:7",
      "text": "For if the truth of God hath more abounded through my lie unto his glory; why yet am I also judged as a sinner?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:8",
      "text": "And not rather, (as we be slanderously reported, and as some affirm that we say,) Let us do evil, that good may come? whose damnation is just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:9",
      "text": "What then? are we better than they? No, in no wise: for we have before proved both Jews and Gentiles, that they are all under sin;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:10",
      "text": "As it is written, There is none righteous, no, not one:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:11",
      "text": "There is none that understandeth, there is none that seeketh after God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:12",
      "text": "They are all gone out of the way, they are together become unprofitable; there is none that doeth good, no, not one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:13",
      "text": "Their throat is an open sepulchre; with their tongues they have used deceit; the poison of asps is under their lips:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:14",
      "text": "Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:15",
      "text": "Their feet are swift to shed blood:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:16",
      "text": "Destruction and misery are in their ways:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:17",
      "text": "And the way of peace have they not known:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:18",
      "text": "There is no fear of God before their eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:19",
      "text": "Now we know that what things soever the law saith, it saith to them who are under the law: that every mouth may be stopped, and all the world may become guilty before God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:20",
      "text": "Therefore by the deeds of the law there shall no flesh be justified in his sight: for by the law is the knowledge of sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:21",
      "text": "But now the righteousness of God without the law is manifested, being witnessed by the law and the prophets;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:22",
      "text": "Even the righteousness of God which is by faith of Jesus Christ unto all and upon all them that believe: for there is no difference:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:23",
      "text": "For all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:24",
      "text": "Being justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:25",
      "text": "Whom God hath set forth to be a propitiation through faith in his blood, to declare his righteousness for the remission of sins that are past, through the forbearance of God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:26",
      "text": "To declare, I say, at this time his righteousness: that he might be just, and the justifier of him which believeth in Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:27",
      "text": "Where is boasting then? It is excluded. By what law? of works? Nay: but by the law of faith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:28",
      "text": "Therefore we conclude that a man is justified by faith without the deeds of the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:29",
      "text": "Is he the God of the Jews only? is he not also of the Gentiles? Yes, of the Gentiles also:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:30",
      "text": "Seeing it is one God, which shall justify the circumcision by faith, and uncircumcision through faith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:romans.3.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 3:31",
      "text": "Do we then make void the law through faith? God forbid: yea, we establish the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
